betterquesting:10.desc:8: Look around in the crates for a way to open the door!

After you enter the main station area, you might be able to piece together a suit with a small amount of oxygen left.

Before going exploring, you may want to use the command "§6/sethome§r", just in case you fall! Once set, your home can be teleported to by using the command "§6/home§r".
Once you've found the §aCrowbar§r by looting various storages, use it on some of the blocks making up your walkway and the crates around.
This Crowbar is much sturdier then the previous version, and can disassemble many more block types.
Smash them on the ground to recover some of the useful components!
Smash them on the ground to recover some of the useful components!

These are found after harvesting other blocks for the plating.

Smash them on the ground to recover some of the useful components!

You find yourself on a ship, lost in space.


Enter one of these commands to begin:

§6/station create§r - If playing by yourself or starting a team.
§6§a/station invite [player]§r - The invite command asks another player to join your island.
§a§2/station join§r - The join command will have you join an island if recently asked by the invite command.
Split your Iron into nuggets and cook them again for Wrought Iron.

You'll need at least a second §6Output Bus§r on the Station Recycler in order to get Rubber Scrap from processing §aSimple Internals§r. 

If you only have 2 buses, you will need to toggle §cVoid Item§r mode in the controller in order to start the craft.

You'll need to craft up the other tools to move forward!

§6Sticks can be aquired by smashing Dead Bushes on the ground.

Once you have the Generator back up and running, you'll be able to process materials much more efficiently and with less stress.

You'll also need 23 casings to complete the structure.
You may have noticed that you won't be able to recharge the §6Rusty Batteries§r, so creating your own source of rechargeable energy storage is next.

3x3 Crafting!

This also links to adjacent inventories for crafting and can save up to 9 recipes!
With access to a method of pulverization, you'll be able to mix a few basic alloys.
If you end up getting low on power, you'll be able to keep the lights on with this.
§aGreen Crystals§r are used in some more advanced alloys, while §cRed Crystals§r can smelt 32 items each!
With these, you'll be able to complete the Recycler and start making more complex materials!
If you look around the ship, you'll be able to find some tools to help you get started.
Craft up a Copper or Iron Furnace for your basic Smelting Needs!
You can smash some of the Glass found around the ship in crates into dust.
Until you can craft conveyers on your own, you'll have to rely on good old fasioned Looting!
You can use anything to contain the oxygen when you go exploring, but these are fancy!
